    {
      "id": 45145,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "\nHi @security,\n\n_Steps:_\n\n1-The affected program is enabled with a Hacker Facing Custom Fields feature:\nhttps://hackerone.com/:handle/custom_fields\n\n`Custom Fields`   >>   `Hacker Facing Custom Fields`  >>`new field with a title name (hello)`  >>    \n`Select type : text`  >>  `Visibility; Hacker facing - this field will appear on the report for the hacker to complete`\n\n2-Then a malicious user report a bug to that program and put this payload `\"><img src=x onerror=alert(document.domain)>`\nto Additional information field in the report and then submit the report.\n\n3-when the program admin open the attacker report and doing this actions [edit or modify or change and save it] to the value of the attacker in report(Custom data - hacker facing)  field as a result a stored  xss issue happen.\n{F1277066}\n\nPoc:\nhttps://hackerone.com/reports/1173040#activity-11548302\n\n-----\n\ni think this issue happen when rendering the report data via : ==updated custom field (from) `the attacker value` (to) `a new value`   both values in (from) & (to) are not sanitized from malicious code so the attacker malicious payload executed there.==\n\n{F1277062}\n\n==so even if the program admin have changed the attacker payload in the report (Custom data - hacker facing) field in order to prevent the attacker code from execute, the attacker payload will be saved in the report data for ever in `(from) value` and the attack going to work permanently.==\n\n---------------------------------------------------\n\n\n",
      "updated_at": "2021-11-21T15:47:54.913Z",
      "can_view?": true,
      "can_create?": false,
